Big flavor. A massive hit at the party we threw last night and a personal hit with me because they're so easy to make. I assembled the kebabs ahead of time and then we just threw on the grill when guests arrived. They cooked up so quickly that there was no need to bother with the lemon/oil basting. Just squeeze some lemon directly over them when they're finished. Oh, and keep the cubes of chicken small. The marinade is paste-like, and with smaller cubes, there is a fantastic flavor-to-meat ratio. The mint is the real kicker. People kept asking "Is this mint?!" It curls over the chicken when you grill it, so it ends up being this perfect mint-chicken-onion mouthful.

