You know how sometimes you make recipes and they end up not being very flavorful or you think "that wasn't worth the work." This is definitely _not_ one of those recipes. It's absolutely excellent. The garlic/spice mixture is paste-like so it really coats the chicken, and if you do small, one-inch cubes as the recipe recommends, then the flavor-to-meat ratio is really strong. Also, this is _ideal_ party food. You can assemble the kebabs ahead of time and they grill up likety-split. So quick in fact that I don't recommend bothering with the olive oil/lemon baste that the recipe calls for. Just squeeze some lemon over top of them when they're finished. We tripled the recipe for a party last night and people absolutely scarfed them down.

