Rating: 0
Alaska: That is not an authentic Greek cucumber sauce, known as "tzatziki". The real stuff (which is awesome on EVERYTHING) is: 1 carton yogurt (full fat, drained overnight in cheesecloth to make "yogurt cheese"), 1 cucumber, peeled, seeded (this is a must) and grated, garlic crushed (to taste but at least 2 cloves), 2-4 TBS olive oil, S/P, dill. Mix and let sit in the fridge for a couple of hours. Real Greek tzatziki doesn't contain tomato like the recipes on this site imply. Lived in Greece, this is it. Enjoy :)

